<br>
<br>
Day 1 - PoV<br>
Crystalline golems, spiders, and eventually frogs and larvae<br>
Total grind time 7 hours<br>
parchments 2<br>
<br>
Day 2 - PoV<br>
Golems and spiders<br>
Total grind time 6 hours<br>
parchments 2<br>
<br>
Day 2, later on; PoV doing flag for HoH (raid numbers)<br>
Golems on the way to HoH <br>
Time approx 1 hour, mobs kill approx 50<br>
Parchments 4 (including dragon drops)<br>
<br>
Day 3, PoD doing flag for CoD (raid numbers)<br>
1-1.5 hours time.<br>
Around 75+ mobs killed, various levels<br>
Parchments 3 including Grummus drops<br>
<br>
Day 4<br>
Mobs = Valorian guards <br>
Total time 6 hours<br>
Spectral parchments x 1<br>
<br>
Like I said, don't know how things have been for everyone else after the patch, but I've seen few parchment drops for the number of hours invested.  <br>
<br>
IMHO Varant has screwed up spell drops before (i.e. Kunark) then 6 months later said &quot;oops they should now be working as intended&quot;.  Remember 54 water pet, Velocity, Muzzle of mardu... they sure weren't working as intended.  Level 60 pet heal... hmm only seen 2 after many burrower, THO, AL, XTC, and Emp kills... Elnerick's Electrical Rending, Garrison's superior sundering... drop like candy.<br>
  <br>
I don't expect parchments to be dropping out of the sky, but each caster should leave with 1 parchment after a 6 hour grind, especially in the absense of any decent coin/wearable loot.  Others in my guild report seeing less than what I describe above.<br>
<br>
My appoligies for this turning in to a bit of a rant, but spell drops have been a sore issue with me in the past.  Perhaps I'm unlucky, how's things been for you guys post patch?<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p>Master Caldywen Lebeau &lt;BR&gt;<br>
